article_title: No injuries in officer-involved accident in north Wichita
article_text:
An officer-involved accident in north Wichita early Saturday morning caused some significant damage to both vehicles involved.

It happened around 2:30 a.m. in the southbound lanes of I-135 at 21st Street North.

Dispatchers say the officer was responding to an "officer in trouble" call when it happened, but the specific details surrounding the accident weren't made available.

No one was hurt.
